Defined eval metrics: - name: Failure Mode Coverage (FMC)
- maximize: False
- description: Failure Mode Coverage is a metric that measures the completeness 
with which a test or evaluation can uncover failure modes in an autonomous 
driving system. It is calculated by identifying the number of distinct failure 
modes observed during testing (such as misclassifications, false 
positives/negatives, bias in decision-making, etc.), and comparing this to the 
total number of unique failure modes that have been theoretically identified or 
are known to occur based on previous research and real-world incidents. Lower 
values indicate that the testing/evaluation has a high capability to identify 
failure modes, thus contributing to the improvement of the autonomous driving 
system's robustness.
